name: Colour in Motion Art Greetings Card supporting Breast Cancer Care
description:
15% + VAT of each card sold donated to Breast Cancer Care

‘Colour in Motion 5368′
A6 Art Greetings Card printed on 330 micron Trucard FSC Certified
white envelope, blank inside, individually wrapped

Breast Cancer Care

Breast Cancer Care’s Director of Fundraising, Judy Beard, said, “One person is diagnosed with breast cancer in the UK every 10 minutes which is a shocking statistic.  We want to be there for each and every person and their friends and families too.  That’s why we are so grateful for the support of Elizabeth James Art, as without people like them we simply couldn’t continue to provide our free services. Thank you.”

Breast cancer is the most common cancer in the UK. Breast Cancer Care’s vision is that every person affected by breast cancer receives the best possible treatment, information and support. From diagnosis, through treatment and beyond, they are the only UK-wide charity dedicated to providing round-the-clock emotional and practical support to anyone affected; this includes friends and family too.  

Breast Cancer Care provides national, regional and local services. Their free Helpline, information-packed website and online discussion forums offer expert guidance.  Across the UK, they also offer skilled emotional and practical support through a range of confidential, face-to-face services. You can find out more at www.breastcancercare.org.uk

Breast Cancer Care is here for anyone affected by breast cancer.
Visit www.breastcancercare.org.uk or call our free helpline on 
0808 800 6000
Registered charity in England and Wales 1017658, Registered charity in Scotland SC038104
